In Confluence, when we upgrade the license to reach a high user tier, we will need to also update our add-ons to match with the content of the license. However, Confluence does not provide any notifications about the requested changes. 

This is a suggestion to notify the administrator when the add-ons will request an update to match with the license needed. For example, the user haves a 250 users license and would like to upgrade it to 500. When pasting the upgraded license under *Licensing Information*, Confluence would display a popup with add-ons that would also request an upgrade, prior to using the license.

