When trying to access elements of an array in an Apache Velocity template via the {{get}} method (a true array object, not an ArrayList wrapper, automatically created in some cases, e.g. when instantiating a VTL array literal), a NullPointerException is thrown in the uberspect code that Confluence brings along ({{com.atlassian.confluence.velocity.introspection.ConfluenceAnnotationBoxingUberspect}} and related classes).

Example template:

{code}
#set($list = ['hello', 'world'])
#set($arr = $list.toArray())
$arr.get(1)
{code}

When using a plain Velocity engine, i.e. one with which {{ConfluenceAnnotationBoxingUberspect}} has *not* been registered, the template renders just fine and behaves as described in the Velocity documentation.

Iteration works, but direct access via {{get}} does not.

Here's a Java code snippet to reproduce the issue:

{code}
String template = ""
        + "#set($list = ['hello', 'world'])\n"
        + "#set($arr = $list.toArray())\n"
        + "$arr.get(1)";
        
VelocityEngine engine = new VelocityEngine();
engine.setProperty(RuntimeConstants.UBERSPECT_CLASSNAME, ConfluenceAnnotationBoxingUberspect.class.getName());
engine.init();

StringWriter writer = new StringWriter();
engine.evaluate(new VelocityContext(), writer, "", template);
String output = writer.toString();

assertEquals("world", output);
{code}

The following two questions on Atlassian Answers seem to be related to this issue:

from 2011: https://answers.atlassian.com/questions/25758/using-arrays-in-velocity
from 2015: https://answers.atlassian.com/questions/24661135/failure-accessing-array-elements-from-velocity

To work around the problem, one can copy the elements of the array into an ArrayList:

{code}
#macro(toList $collection)
  #set($tmp = [])
  #foreach($item in $collection)
  	#set($changed = $tmp.add($item))
  #end
  #set($collection = $tmp)
#end

#set($list = ['hello', 'world'])
#set($arr = $list.toArray())
#toList($arr)
$arr.get(1)
{code}

Tested with the ConfluenceAnnotationBoxingUberspect versions found in Confluence 5.3.0 and Confluence 5.9.12 and with Velocity version 1.6 (not 1.7, although it may be an issue there as well).

