Large instances that have lots of active users will produce lots of comments. There are also valid use cases for lots of comments on an announcements page.

Currently, the number of comments on a page can get quite unwieldy, which makes Confluence slower than normal. It'd be nice if pages with large numbers of comments could be paginated, or have an "infinite load mode" to reduce the number of comments that are loaded at any one time.

This issue was raised as https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONF-25774, however it was closed due to a lack of customer feedback. As teams grow in size and complexity, we should revisit this issue.
